Nero Claudius Drusus the younger of the two sons of Livia Drusilla, by her first husband, Tiberius Claudius N ero, was born in Augustus’ house, rac. 38, three months after his mother’s divorse and renrnrriage. He was byfar the most popular of the two brothers. ln ac. 16, when Augustus set out for Gaul, taking with him Tiberius, who was praetor at the time, Drusus was appointed to discharge the duties of the office during his brother's absence (Dio 54. 19). Of his expedition in the following year against the Raeti, some account will be found in the Introd. to this Book. He died, six years afterwards, from the effect of a fall from his horse, while engaged in the last of three campaigns beyond the Rhine, which gained for him the posthumous title of Germanicus.
